definition: any of several brassicas (Brassica oleracea) of European origin, a leafy garden plant (Brassica oleracea capitata) with a short stem and a dense globular head of usually green leaves that is used as a vegetable
any of several plants related to or resembling cabbage
pieces of cloth left in cutting out garments and traditionally kept by tailors as perquisites

examples: They also cabbaged our bats, balls, and gloves.
